Subject: [PATCH 1/7] Rename Engineering department to Detailing

Same department (code ENG unchanged), just the display name - so this
is a pure data change via db:seed, no migration needed. Also updated
the two hardcoded 'Engineering' fallback labels used for a unit's
currentStage before it's assigned to an actual department, so they
say 'Detailing' too instead of creating a mismatch with the renamed
department.

NOT renamed, flagging for confirmation rather than guessing: the
separate "Engineering Dashboard" page/workflow (EngineeringStatus enum,
the Submittal/Design/Drawings/Programming sequential approval steps).
That's a distinct concept from the department itself - a much bigger
change (schema enum, migration, several UI surfaces) that wasn't
explicitly requested. Say the word if you want that renamed too.

Note on the previous reorder: the sidebar order you asked for
(Purchasing, Engineering, Fabrication, Assembly, Piping, Electrical,
Painting, Testing, Shipping) was already correctly sitting in seed.ts
from the last patch - the screenshot showing the old order strongly
suggests db:seed was never re-run after applying it. A git patch only
changes the seed script's source code; it doesn't touch the live
database until the script actually executes. Re-running db:seed now
will apply both the already-pending reorder and this rename together.
