Subject: [PATCH 2/7] Item 1: Detailing/Engineering stage progress now visible
 on department boards

Root cause: Engineering's approval stages (Submittal Received, Design
Completed, etc.) are tracked entirely on Unit.engineeringStatus - there
was never a real ProductionTask behind them, since there's no process
route for a department that doesn't fabricate anything. That meant
clicking "Mark Submittal Received" on the Engineering Dashboard did
something real, but it was structurally invisible everywhere else -
the Detailing department's column on Shop Floor and Supervisor
Dashboard was always empty, full stop.

Rather than restructure the whole engineering workflow into the task
system (a much bigger, riskier change touching a working page), added
synthesized read-only entries: any unit currently between
SubmittalReceived and ProgrammingCompleted (NotStarted has no button
pressed yet, ReleasedToManufacturing has moved on to Fabrication) shows
up in the Detailing column with its current stage as the "process"
label. These aren't real tasks - TaskCard now checks an isSynthetic
flag to skip the Complete button entirely (that's not how engineering
stages advance) and route a click to the unit page instead of trying
to open a task drawer for a task id that doesn't exist.
---
