From c0538d370a0f3b8b9e6c374984306d285c01e65f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 14:45:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/7] Item 2: side-by-side process/station columns, reorderable
 on Supervisor Dashboard

When viewing a single department (e.g. Fabrication via the admin
sidebar link, or on Supervisor Dashboard), each process/station
(Cutting, Bending, Foaming) is now its own column shown side by side,
instead of stacked vertically inside one narrow column - directly
addresses "see all the processes... side by side."

Split deliberately by page:
- Shop Floor Dashboard: side-by-side layout only, no drag capability
  at all - it must stay a passive viewing board per the standing rule
  from earlier this session (no click, no drag, ever, full stop).
- Supervisor Dashboard: same side-by-side layout, PLUS drag-to-reorder
  station columns by their header ("let me place the things where I
  like"), persisted to localStorage per department so the arrangement
  is remembered next time. This is the interactive page, so this is
  where customization actually belongs.

I caught myself building the draggable version on Shop Floor first by
mistake and corrected it before committing - flagging that explicitly
since getting that boundary right was the whole point of item 4 from
your last message.
