From 66df3f7e2c1e7fd92a667591172565f54f4d641a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 15:17:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/7] CRITICAL FIX: replace broken $use middleware with a
 stable interceptor

Confirmed by the user's real typecheck output (not something I could
catch in my own sandbox, which lacks a fully generated Prisma client):

  src/common/prisma/prisma.service.ts:42:10 - error TS2339:
  Property '$use' does not exist on type 'PrismaService'.

The earlier Decimal-to-number fix used PrismaService.$use() middleware.
That API is fully removed in this project's Prisma version (6.19.3) -
not deprecated-but-working, actually gone from the type surface
entirely. That fix could never have worked as shipped.

Replaced with a NestJS response interceptor (DecimalTransformInterceptor)
instead - a stable, non-Prisma-version-dependent API that converts
Decimal instances to plain numbers on the way out of every response.
Registered in main.ts AFTER ClassSerializerInterceptor specifically -
Nest runs later-registered interceptors' response transforms first
(closer to the raw handler output), so this order makes Decimal
conversion happen before class-transformer's instanceToPlain() ever
sees a raw Decimal to mangle. Swapping that order would silently break
the fix again.

PrismaService reverts to a plain PrismaClient subclass with no custom
constructor logic - the conversion no longer lives there at all.
---
